  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b9f \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf, \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Special meeting with major party leaders led by Sajith - Maithiri, Vicky etc. participated",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Maithripala Sirisena, former president and leader of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party, was present at a special discussion held at the opposition leader's office in Colombo under the leadership of opposition leader Sajith Premadasa.",
        "Organized by United People's Shakti Member of Parliament Budhika Patirana, the discussion was themed 'Meeting on National Policies and Future Action'.",
        "When asked the Deputy President of the Tamil Progressive Alliance Velusathi Radhakrishnan about the issue that was brought to attention during this,",
        "The theme of the discussion was 'Meeting on National Policies and Future Actions' and detailed attention was paid to the reforms to be carried out in the 22nd Constitutional Amendment. It was attended by all parties interested in the National Seer Amendments.",
        "During this, there was a wide consultation on the ideas presented by the Leader of the Opposition Sajith Premadasa and the civil organizations.",
        "Each party who participated in the discussion on national reforms shared their views and ideas.",
        "He said that attention was paid to the principles to be included in the 22nd constitutional amendment to eliminate corruption and fraud.",
        "Civil activists including Vigden Ivar, Gamini Viyangoda, KW Janaranjana, Tamil Progressive Alliance President Mano Ganesan, Vice Presidents V. Iradhakrishnan, Palani Digambaram, Sri Lanka Muslim Congress President Raup Hakeem, Tamil People's National Alliance President CV Wickineswaran and many others. It is noteworthy that the Mukistas participated in this discussion."
      ],
